w technologies and the adoption of new technologies so that we can free ourselves from the non-market opec stranglehold on energy in this country." </p><p>... </p><p>moran: "as he ends this campaign day with a lot more ahead of him, (candidate full) seems full of hope. hope that (PARTY NAME)s and americans, in general, are ready for a new face, a pretty handsome one at that, and a new voice, a voice that just happens to belong to a mormon." </p><p><b> <u>governor (candidate full) on his faith:</u> </b> </p><p>moran: "but there's something else about (candidate full), something that makes him different from every other candidate. he's a mormon. would you describe yourself as a devout mormon? true believer?" </p><p>governor (candidate last): "absolutely. i'm proud of my faith. it's part of my heritage. i think the american people respect individuals of faith. that's the kind of person they wanna lead the country." </p><p><b> <u>governor (candidate full) on his pro-life record:</u> </b> </p><p>moran: "what's your position on abortion?" </p><p>governor (candidate last): "i'm pro-life." </p><p>... </p><p>moran: "your critics say you're flip-flopping rather conveniently when you're running for president." </p><p>governor (candidate last): "well, you know, we all learn from experience. and i'm just like other people in this nation. not everything i believed 12 or 13 years ago is the same today, with regards to the issue of abortion. and so about two years ago, i said i am pro-life. and prior to that time, i had a different position." </p><p><b> <u>governor (candidate full) on iraq:</u> </b> </p><p>moran: "was it the right thing for the united states to invade iraq?" </p><p>governor (candidate last): "well, i supported the president at the time. he indicated that based on intelligence, we had weapons of mass destruction, a threat to this land. he proposed a solution and i supported it. and i'm not going back in trying to second-guess that. i don't have the data or inside sources to suggest doing that." </p><p>... </p><p>governor (candidate last): "there's no question about the fact that we have not conducted the war as effectively as we might ... and it's been problematic and has caused part of the problems we face today."</p></span>



